I believe that ,if it has not already been done, it is important that you know that you will always meet people who will not necessarily agree with your choices, who will not like your style, your facial expressions or I don't know what else... but, never stop believing in yourself, stay true to yourself, with your personality and sensitivity that convinced the jury; Another thing, it is not given to everyone to dare! It will allow you to move forward and we can only note that you fit in with any repertoire, I even find your versions sometimes better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you were not part of what I would have bet on at the beginning and sincerely, I do not remember not having enjoyed one of your performances, you surprise me... to finish, I loved your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I had also loved the original but for once I heard the lyrics clearly, we had perhaps the impression that you were careful not to make any facial expressions, you transmitted emotion to me through my television so I do not understand why 3 members of the jury did not feel it! Well, I wish you many beautiful things, keep your feet on the ground, do not change anything to what you are, stay humble, stay you, make good use of constructive criticism and do not pay attention to those that are not.
